    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "About ALSO.\n\nWe’re ALSO, an electric mobility company originally conceived as a part of Rivian. We’re a passionate team of builders, dreamers, doers and innovators, focused on creating entirely new (not to mention, innovative and delightful) vertically integrated, small EVs designed to meet the global mobility challenges of today and tomorrow. Our mission is to inspire everyone to ride ALSO—replacing many local car, truck and SUV miles with ones on vehicles that are more affordable, more enjoyable and 10-50x more efficient.\n\nJoin us at a pivotal moment in our journey. As one of the early hires, you’ll play a critical role in shaping the digital experience of our connected e-bike product. This is a greenfield opportunity in a fast-paced, venture-backed startup environment where you will contribute to key decisions, own critical user experiences, and work closely with a small, highly motivated team. We’re building a premium customer experience—from purchase to ride—and you’ll be central to that mission. You’ll have the autonomy to design elegant, scalable systems and the support to grow alongside a rapidly evolving company.\n\nWhat you will do\n\n - Build, and maintain scalable integrations across our Shopify-based e-commerce, logistics, and account systems, ensuring a seamless user experience.\n\n - Build APIs and backend services that connect our mobile app, third-party platforms, and internal tools.\n\n - Collaborate cross-functionally with product, design, data, and operations teams to bring a seamless multi-platform experience to life.\n\n - Ship high-quality, maintainable code and continuously improve engineering practices through documentation, code reviews, and refactoring.\n\n - Contribute to growing our engineering culture by introducing best practices and fostering a mindset of continuous learning and improvement.\n\nWhat you bring\n\nRequired\n\n - Strong Shopify experience (Liquid, Storefront API, Admin API, Functions, App development)\n\n - Backend development in Node.js or Go in the AWS ecosystem.\n\n - Experience with event-driven systems (webhooks, queues, EventBridge, SQS, etc.)\n\n - Comfortable with relational databases (Postgres/MySQL)\n\n - Good understanding of E-commerce flows: orders, carts, payments, refunds, RMA\n\n - Demonstrated success in a 0→1 setting, ideally in a startup or highly autonomous role.\n\n - Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal; able to build trust and drive alignment across technical and non-technical teams.\n\nBonus:\n\n - Frontend development experience (React, modern UI frameworks).\n\n - AWS services (Lambda, EventBridge, SQS, DynamoDB), NetSuite/Celigo\n\nThe salary for this position ranges from $160,000 - $210,000 per year, depending on experience and qualifications.\n\nWhy ALSO.\n\nWe’re passionate about helping the world find a better way to get there—wherever it is you’re headed.\n\nWe’re located in the heart of Silicon Valley and have brought together a world-class team from some of the biggest brands in the technology, automotive, cycling, outdoor recreation and retail spaces. \n\nTogether we’re working hands-on to imagine, design and build an entirely new solution to a global set of transportation challenges. \n\nPerks and Benefits\n\n - Robust health coverage. Excellent health, dental and vision insurance covered up to 100% by ALSO with FSA \u0026 HSA options.\n\n - One Medical membership and dedicated insurance advocates.\n\n - Rich fertility and family building benefits with Progyny.\n\n - Flexible time off. \n\n - 401(k) match.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
